121//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
122const char* Mpeg4_Meta_Kind(int32u Kind)
123{
124 switch (Kind)
125 {
126 case 0x00 : return "Binary";
127 case 0x01 : return "UTF8";
128 case 0x02 : return "UTF16";
129 case 0x03 : return "Mac String";
130 case 0x0E : return "Jpeg";
131 case 0x15 : return "Signed Integer"; //the size of the integer is derived from the container size
132 case 0x16 : return "Float 32";
133 case 0x17 : return "Float 64";
134 default : return "";
135 }
136}
137
138//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
139const char* Mpeg4_TypeModifierName(int32u TypeModifierName)
140{
141 switch (TypeModifierName)
142 {
143 case 0x01 : return "Matrix";
144 case 0x02 : return "Clip";
145 case 0x03 : return "Volume";
146 case 0x04 : return "Audio balance";
147 case 0x05 : return "Graphic mode";
148 case 0x06 : return "Matrix object";
149 case 0x07 : return "Graphics mode object";
150 case 0x76696465 : return "Image type";
151 default : return "";
152 }
153}

161 "reserved",
162};

168 "other samples depend on this one (not disposable)",
169 "no other sample depends on this one (disposable)",
170 "reserved",
171};

182//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
183Ztring Mpeg4_Vendor(int32u Vendor)
184{
185 switch (Vendor)
186 {
187 case 0x46464D50 : return __T("FFMpeg");
188 case 0x4D4F544F : return __T("Motorola");
189 case 0x50484C50 : return __T("Philips");
190 case 0x6170706C : return __T("Apple");
191 case 0x6E6F6B69 : return __T("Nokia");
192 case 0x6D6F746F : return __T("Motorola");
193 default : return Ztring().From_CC4(Vendor);
194 }
195}
196
197//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
198const char* Mpeg4_chan(int16u Ordering)
199{
200 //Source: http://developer.apple.com/library/mac/#documentation/MusicAudio/Reference/CACoreAudioReference/CoreAudioTypes/CompositePage.html
201 //Arbitrary decision (0° = Front):
202 //Front = 0°-80°
203 //Side = 80°-120°
204 //Rear = 120°-180°
205 switch(Ordering)
206 {
207 case 100 : return "Front: C";
208 case 101 : return "Front: L R";
209 case 102 : return "Front: L R (Headphones)"; //With headphones
210 case 103 : return "Front: L R (Matrix)"; //With matrix
211 case 104 : return "Front: C S";
212 case 105 : return "Front: X Y";
213 case 106 : return "Front: L R (Binaural)";
214 case 107 : return "Front: W X Y Z";
215 case 108 : return "Front: L R, Side: L R";
216 case 109 : return "Front: L C R, Rear: L R";
217 case 110 : return "Front: L C R, Rear: L C R";
218 case 111 : return "Front: L C R, Side: L R, Rear: L C R";
219 case 112 : return "Front: L R, TopFront: L R, Rear: L R, TopRear: L R";
220 case 113 : return "Front: L C R";
221 case 114 : return "Front: L C R";
222 case 115 : return "Front: L C R, Rear: C";
223 case 116 : return "Front: L C R, Rear: C";
224 case 117 : return "Front: L C R, Side: L R";
225 case 118 : return "Front: L C R, Side: L R";
226 case 119 : return "Front: L C R, Side: L R";
227 case 120 : return "Front: L C R, Side: L R";
228 case 121 : return "Front: L C R, Side: L R, LFE";
229 case 122 : return "Front: L C R, Side: L R, LFE";
230 case 123 : return "Front: L C R, Side: L R, LFE";
231 case 124 : return "Front: L C R, Side: L R, LFE";
232 case 125 : return "Front: L C R, Side: L C R";
233 case 126 : return "Front: L Lc C Rc R, Side: L R";
234 case 127 : return "Front: L Lc Rc R, Side: L R, LFE";
235 case 128 : return "Front: L C R, Side: L R, Rear: L R, LFE";
236 case 129 : return "Front: L C R, Side: L R, Rear: L R, LFE";
237 case 130 : return "Front: L C R, Side: L R, LF, Front: L R (Matrix)";
238 case 131 : return "Front: L R, Rear: C";
239 case 132 : return "Front: L R, Side: L R";
240 case 133 : return "Front: L R, LFE";
241 case 134 : return "Front: L R, Rear: C, LFE";
242 case 135 : return "Front: L C R, Side: L R, LFE";
243 case 136 : return "Front: L C R, LFE";
244 case 137 : return "Front: L C R, Rear: C, LFE";
245 case 138 : return "Front: L R, Rear: L R, LFE";
246 case 139 : return "Front: L C R, Rear: L R, LFE";
247 case 140 : return "Front: L C R, Side: L R, Rear: L R";
248 case 141 : return "Front: L C R, Side: L R, Rear: C";
249 case 142 : return "Front: L C R, Side: L R, Rear: C, LFE";
250 case 143 : return "Front: L C R, Side: L R, Rear: L R";
251 case 144 : return "Front: L C R, Side: L R, Rear: L C R";
252 case 145 : return "Front: Lw L C R Rw, TopFront: L C R, Side: L R, Rear: L C Cd R, LFE: L R"; //d=direct, all must be confirmed
253 case 146 : return "Front: Lw L Lc C Rc R Rw, TopFront: L C R, Side: L R, Rear: L C Cd R, LFE: L R, HI, VI, Haptic"; //d=direct, all must be confirmed
254 default : return "";
255 }
256}
257
258//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
259const char* Mpeg4_chan_Layout(int16u Ordering)
260{
261 //Source: http://developer.apple.com/library/mac/#documentation/MusicAudio/Reference/CACoreAudioReference/CoreAudioTypes/CompositePage.html
262 // L - left
263 // R - right
264 // C - center
265 // Ls - left surround
266 // Rs - right surround
267 // Cs - center surround
268 // Rls - rear left surround
269 // Rrs - rear right surround
270 // Lw - left wide
271 // Rw - right wide
272 // Lsd - left surround direct
273 // Rsd - right surround direct
274 // Lc - left center
275 // Rc - right center
276 // Ts - top surround
277 // Vhl - vertical height left
278 // Vhc - vertical height center
279 // Vhr - vertical height right
280 // Lt - left matrix total. for matrix encoded stereo.
281 // Rt - right matrix total. for matrix encoded stereo.
282 switch(Ordering)
283 {
284 case 100 : return "C";
285 case 101 : return "L R";
286 case 102 : return "L R"; //With headphones
287 case 103 : return "Lt Rt"; //L R with matrix
288 case 104 : return "M S";
289 case 105 : return "X Y";
290 case 106 : return "L R";
291 case 107 : return "W X Y Z";
292 case 108 : return "L R Ls Rs";
293 case 109 : return "L R Lrs Rrs C";
294 case 110 : return "L R Lrs Rrs C Cs";
295 case 111 : return "L R Lrs Rrs C Crs, Ls, Rs";
296 case 112 : return "L R Lrs Rrs Vhl Vhr, Vhlrs, Vhrrs";
297 case 113 : return "L R C";
298 case 114 : return "C L R";
299 case 115 : return "L R C Cs";
300 case 116 : return "C L R Cs";
301 case 117 : return "L R C Ls Rs";
302 case 118 : return "L R Ls Rs C";
303 case 119 : return "L C R Ls Rs";
304 case 120 : return "C L R Ls Rs";
305 case 121 : return "L R C LFE Ls Rs";
306 case 122 : return "L R Ls Rs C LFE";
307 case 123 : return "L C R Ls Rs LFE";
308 case 124 : return "C L R Ls Rs LFE";
309 case 125 : return "L R C LFE Ls Rs Cs";
310 case 126 : return "L R C LFE Ls Rs Lc Rc";
311 case 127 : return "C Lc Rc L R Ls Rs LFE";
312 case 128 : return "L R C LFE Ls R Rls Rrs";
313 case 129 : return "L R Ls Rs C LFE Lc Rc";
314 case 130 : return "L R C LFE Ls Rs Lt Rt";
315 case 131 : return "L R Cs";
316 case 132 : return "L R Ls Rs";
317 case 133 : return "L R LFE";
318 case 134 : return "L R LFE Cs";
319 case 135 : return "L R LFE Ls Rs";
320 case 136 : return "L R C LFE";
321 case 137 : return "L R C LFE Cs";
322 case 138 : return "L R Ls Rs LFE";
323 case 139 : return "L R Ls Rs C Cs";
324 case 140 : return "L R Ls Rs C Rls Rrs";
325 case 141 : return "C L R Ls Rs Cs ";
326 case 142 : return "C L R Ls Rs Cs LFE";
327 case 143 : return "C L R Ls Rs Rls Rrs";
328 case 144 : return "C L R Ls Rs Rls Rrs Cs";
329 case 145 : return "L R C Vhc Lsd Rsd Ls Rs Vhl Vhr Lw Rw Csd Cs LFE1 LFE2";
330 case 146 : return "L R C Vhc Lsd Rsd Ls Rs Vhl Vhr Lw Rw Csd Cs LFE1 LFE2 Lc Rc HI VI Haptic";
331 case 147 : return "";
332 default : return "";
333 }
334}
335
336//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
337std::string Mpeg4_chan_ChannelDescription (int64u ChannelLabels)
338{
339 std::string Text;
340 if ((ChannelLabels&0x000E)!=0x0000)
341 Text+="Front:";
342 if (ChannelLabels&0x0002)
343 Text+=" L";
344 if (ChannelLabels&0x0008)
345 Text+=" C";
346 if (ChannelLabels&0x0004)
347 Text+=" R";
348
349 if ((ChannelLabels&0x0C00)!=0x0000)
350 {
351 if (!Text.empty())
352 Text+=", ";
353 Text+="Side:";
354 }
355 if (ChannelLabels&0x0400)
356 Text+=" L";
357 if (ChannelLabels&0x0800)
358 Text+=" R";
359
360 if ((ChannelLabels&0x0260)!=0x0000)
361 {
362 if (!Text.empty())
363 Text+=", ";
364 Text+="Back:";
365 }
366 if (ChannelLabels&0x0020)
367 Text+=" L";
368 if (ChannelLabels&0x0200)
369 Text+=" C";
370 if (ChannelLabels&0x0040)
371 Text+=" R";
372
373 if ((ChannelLabels&0x0010)!=0x0000)
374 {
375 if (!Text.empty())
376 Text+=", ";
377 Text+="LFE";
378 }
379
380 if (ChannelLabels&0x000000C000000000LL)
381 {
382 if (!Text.empty())
383 Text+=", ";
384 Text+="Front:";
385 }
386 if (ChannelLabels&0x0000004000000000LL)
387 Text+=" L";
388 if (ChannelLabels&0x0000008000000000LL)
389 Text+=" R";
390 if (ChannelLabels&0x000000C000000000LL)
391 Text+=" (Matrix)";
392
393 return Text;
394}

396//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
397const char* Mpeg4_chan_ChannelDescription_Layout (int32u ChannelLabel)
398{
399 switch(ChannelLabel)
400 {
401 case 1 : return "L";
402 case 2 : return "R";
403 case 3 : return "C";
404 case 4 : return "LFE";
405 case 5 : return "Ls";
406 case 6 : return "Rs";
407 case 7 : return "Lc";
408 case 8 : return "Rc";
409 case 9 : return "Cs";
410 case 10 : return "Lsd";
411 case 11 : return "Rsd";
412 case 12 : return "Tcs";
413 case 13 : return "Vhl";
414 case 14 : return "Vhc";
415 case 15 : return "Vhr";
416 case 16 : return "Trs";
417 case 17 : return "Trs";
418 case 18 : return "Trs";
419 case 33 : return "Lrs";
420 case 34 : return "Rrs";
421 case 35 : return "Lw";
422 case 36 : return "Rw";
423 case 37 : return "LFE2";
424 case 38 : return "Lt";
425 case 39 : return "Rt";
426 case 200 : return "W";
427 case 201 : return "X";
428 case 202 : return "Y";
429 case 203 : return "Z";
430 case 204 : return "M";
431 case 205 : return "S";
432 case 206 : return "X";
433 case 207 : return "Y";
434 case 0x10000 : return "Discrete-0";
435 case 0x10001 : return "Discrete-1";
436 case 0x10002 : return "Discrete-2";
437 case 0x10003 : return "Discrete-3";
438 case 0x10004 : return "Discrete-4";
439 case 0x10005 : return "Discrete-5";
440 case 0x10006 : return "Discrete-6";
441 case 0x10007 : return "Discrete-7";
442 case 0x10008 : return "Discrete-8";
443 case 0x10009 : return "Discrete-9";
444 case 0x1000A : return "Discrete-10";
445 case 0x1000B : return "Discrete-11";
446 case 0x1000C : return "Discrete-12";
447 case 0x1000D : return "Discrete-13";
448 case 0x1000E : return "Discrete-14";
449 case 0x1000F : return "Discrete-15";
450 default : return "?";
451 }

454//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
455std::string Mpeg4_chan_ChannelBitmap (int32u ChannelBitmap)
456{
457 std::string Text;
458 if ((ChannelBitmap&0x0007)!=0x0000)
459 Text+="Front:";
460 if (ChannelBitmap&0x0001)
461 Text+=" L";
462 if (ChannelBitmap&0x0004)
463 Text+=" C";
464 if (ChannelBitmap&0x0002)
465 Text+=" R";
466
467 if ((ChannelBitmap&0x0600)!=0x0000)
468 Text+=", Side:";
469 if (ChannelBitmap&0x0200)
470 Text+=" L";
471 if (ChannelBitmap&0x0400)
472 Text+=" R";
473
474 if ((ChannelBitmap&0x0130)!=0x0000)
475 Text+=", Back:";
476 if (ChannelBitmap&0x0010)
477 Text+=" L";
478 if (ChannelBitmap&0x0100)
479 Text+=" C";
480 if (ChannelBitmap&0x0020)
481 Text+=" R";
482
483 if ((ChannelBitmap&0x0008)!=0x0000)
484 Text+=", LFE";
485
486 return Text;
487}
488
489//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
490const char* Mpeg4_chan_ChannelBitmap_Layout (int32u ChannelBitmap)
491{
492 switch(ChannelBitmap)
493 {
494 case 0 : return "L"; // Left
495 case 1 : return "R"; // Right
496 case 2 : return "C"; // Center
497 case 3 : return "LFE"; // LFEScreen
498 case 4 : return "Ls"; // LeftSurround / Back Left
499 case 5 : return "Rs"; // RightSurround / Back Right
500 case 6 : return "?"; // LeftCenter
501 case 7 : return "?"; // RightCenter
502 case 8 : return "Cs"; // CenterSurround / Back Center
503 case 9 : return "Lsd"; // LeftSurroundDirect / Side Left
504 case 10 : return "Rsd"; // RightSurroundDirect / Side Right
505 case 11 : return "?"; // TopCenterSurround
506 case 12 : return "?"; // VerticalHeightLeft / Top Front Left
507 case 13 : return "?"; // VerticalHeightCenter / Top Front Center
508 case 14 : return "?"; // VerticalHeightRight / Top Front Right"
509 case 15 : return "?"; // TopBackLeft
510 case 16 : return "?"; // TopBackCenter
511 case 17 : return "?"; // TopBackRight
512 default : return "?";
513 }
514}

516//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
517const char* Mpeg4_jp2h_METH(int8u METH)
518{
519 switch (METH)
520 {
521 case 0x01 : return "Enumerated colourspace";
522 case 0x02 : return "Restricted ICC profile";
523 default : return "";
524 }
525}

527//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
528const char* Mpeg4_jp2h_EnumCS(int32u EnumCS)
529{
530 switch (EnumCS)
531 {
532 case 0x10 : return "RGB"; //sRGB
533 case 0x11 : return "Y";
534 case 0x12 : return "YUV"; //sYUV
535 default : return "";
536 }
537}

841
842//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
843const char* Mpeg4_Description(int32u Description)
844{
845 switch (Description)
846 {
847 case Elements::moov_trak_mdia_minf_stbl_stsd_xxxx_idfm_atom : return "Classic atom structure";
848 case Elements::moov_trak_mdia_minf_stbl_stsd_xxxx_idfm_qtat : return "QT atom structure";
849 case Elements::moov_trak_mdia_minf_stbl_stsd_xxxx_idfm_fxat : return "Effect";
850 case Elements::moov_trak_mdia_minf_stbl_stsd_xxxx_idfm_priv : return "Private";
851 case Elements::moov_trak_mdia_minf_stbl_stsd_xxxx_idfm_subs : return "Substitute if main codec not available";
852 case Elements::moov_trak_mdia_minf_stbl_stsd_xxxx_idfm_cspc : return "Native pixel format";
853 default : return "";
854 }
855}

857//***************************************************************************
858// Format
859//***************************************************************************
860
861//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
862void File_Mpeg4::Data_Parse()
863{
864 //mdat
865 if (IsParsing_mdat)
866 {
867 mdat_xxxx();
868 return;
869 }
870
871 //Padding
872 if (!Element_Code && !Element_Size)
873 return;
874
875 //Parsing
876 DATA_BEGIN
877 ATOM(bloc)
878 ATOM(cdat)
879 ATOM(cdt2)
880 LIST_SKIP(free)
881 ATOM(ftyp)
882 ATOM(idat)
883 ATOM(idsc)
884 ATOM(jp2c)
885 LIST(jp2h)
886 ATOM_BEGIN
887 ATOM(jp2h_colr)
888 ATOM(jp2h_ihdr)
889 ATOM_END
890 LIST(mdat)
891 ATOM_DEFAULT_ALONE(mdat_xxxx)
892 LIST(mfra)
893 ATOM_BEGIN
894 ATOM(mfra_mfro)
895 ATOM(mfra_tfra)
896 ATOM_END
897 LIST(moof)
898 ATOM_BEGIN
899 ATOM(moof_mfhd)
900 LIST(moof_traf)
901 ATOM_BEGIN
902 ATOM(moof_traf_sdtp)
903 ATOM(moof_traf_tfhd)
904 ATOM(moof_traf_trun)
905 ATOM_END
906 ATOM_END
907 LIST(moov)
908 ATOM_BEGIN
909 ATOM(moov_ainf)
910 LIST(moov_cmov)
911 ATOM_BEGIN
912 ATOM(moov_cmov_dcom)
913 ATOM(moov_cmov_cmvd)
914 ATOM_END
915 ATOM(moov_ctab)
916 ATOM(moov_iods)
917 LIST(moov_meta)
918 ATOM_BEGIN
919 ATOM(moov_meta_bxml)
920 LIST(moov_meta_keys)
921 ATOM_BEGIN
922 ATOM(moov_meta_keys_mdta)
923 ATOM_END
924 ATOM(moov_meta_hdlr)
925 LIST(moov_meta_ilst)
926 LIST_DEFAULT_ALONE_BEGIN (moov_meta_ilst_xxxx)
927 ATOM_BEGIN
928 ATOM (moov_meta_ilst_xxxx_data)
929 ATOM (moov_meta_ilst_xxxx_mean)
930 ATOM (moov_meta_ilst_xxxx_name)
931 ATOM_END
932 LIST_DEFAULT_ALONE_END
933 ATOM(moov_meta_xml)
934 ATOM_END
935 LIST(moov_mvex)
936 ATOM_BEGIN
937 ATOM(moov_mvex_mehd)
938 ATOM(moov_mvex_trex)
939 ATOM_END
940 ATOM(moov_mvhd)
941 LIST(moov_trak)
942 ATOM_BEGIN
943 LIST(moov_trak_edts)
944 ATOM_BEGIN
945 ATOM(moov_trak_edts_elst)
946 ATOM_END
947 ATOM(moov_trak_load)
948 LIST(moov_trak_mdia)
949 ATOM_BEGIN
950 ATOM(moov_trak_mdia_hdlr)
951 LIST(moov_trak_mdia_imap)
952 ATOM_BEGIN
953 LIST(moov_trak_mdia_imap_sean)
954 ATOM_BEGIN
955 LIST(moov_trak_mdia_imap_sean___in)
956 ATOM_BEGIN
957 ATOM(moov_trak_mdia_imap_sean___in___ty)
958 ATOM(moov_trak_mdia_imap_sean___in_dtst)
959 ATOM(moov_trak_mdia_imap_sean___in_obid)
960 ATOM_END
961 ATOM_END
962 ATOM_END
963 ATOM(moov_trak_mdia_mdhd)
964 LIST(moov_trak_mdia_minf)
965 ATOM_BEGIN
966 LIST(moov_trak_mdia_minf_code)
967 ATOM_BEGIN
968 LIST(moov_trak_mdia_minf_code_sean)
969 ATOM_BEGIN
970 ATOM(moov_trak_mdia_minf_code_sean_RU_A)

1209//***************************************************************************
1210// Elements
1211//***************************************************************************
1212
1213#define NAME_VERSION_FLAG(ELEMENT_NAME) \
1214 Element_Name(ELEMENT_NAME); \
1215 int32u Flags; \
1216 int8u Version; \
1217 { \
1218 Get_B1(Version, "Version"); \
1219 Get_B3(Flags, "Flags"); \
1220 } \
1221
1222#define INTEGRITY_VERSION(_VERSION) \
1223 if (Version>_VERSION) \
1224 { \
1225 Skip_XX(Element_Size-Element_Offset, "Unknown data"); \
1226 return; \
1227 } \
1228
1229#define INTEGRITY(TOVALIDATE, ERRORTEXT) \
1230 if (!(TOVALIDATE)) \
1231 { \
1232 Trusted_IsNot(ERRORTEXT); \
1233 return; \
1234 } \
1235
1236#define INTEGRITY_SIZE1(ELEMENT_SIZE0) \
1237 INTEGRITY_VERSION(0); \
1238 if (Element_Size!=ELEMENT_SIZE0+4) \
1239 { \
1240 Trusted_IsNot("Size is wrong"); \
1241 return; \
1242 } \
1243
1244#define INTEGRITY_SIZE2(ELEMENT_SIZE0, ELEMENT_SIZE1) \
1245 INTEGRITY_VERSION(1); \
1246 if (Version==0 && Element_Size!=ELEMENT_SIZE0 \
1247 || Version==1 && Element_Size!=ELEMENT_SIZE1) \
1248 { \
1249 Trusted_IsNot("Size is wrong"); \
1250 return; \
1251 } \
1252
1253#define INTEGRITY_SIZE_ATLEAST1(ELEMENT_SIZE0) \
1254 INTEGRITY_VERSION(0); \
1255 if (Version==0 && Element_Size<ELEMENT_SIZE0) \
1256 { \
1257 Trusted_IsNot("Size is wrong"); \
1258 return; \
1259 } \
1260
1261#define INTEGRITY_SIZE_ATLEAST2(ELEMENT_SIZE0, ELEMENT_SIZE1) \
1262 INTEGRITY_VERSION(1); \
1263 if (Version==0 && Element_Size<ELEMENT_SIZE0 \
1264 || Version==1 && Element_Size<ELEMENT_SIZE1) \
1265 { \
1266 Trusted_IsNot("Size is wrong"); \
1267 return; \
1268 } \
1269
1270#define Get_B_DEPENDOFVERSION(_INFO, _NAME) \
1271 { \
1272 if (Version==0) \
1273 { \
1274 int32u Info; \
1275 Get_B4(Info, _NAME); \
1276 _INFO=Info; \
1277 } \
1278 else \
1279 Get_B8(_INFO, _NAME); \
1280 } \
1281
1282#define Get_DATE1904_DEPENDOFVERSION(_INFO, _NAME) \
1283 { \
1284 if (Version==0) \
1285 { \
1286 int32u Temp; \
1287 Get_B4(Temp, _NAME); \
1288 _INFO.Date_From_Seconds_1904(Temp); \
1289 } \
1290 else \
1291 { \
1292 int64u Temp; \
1293 Get_B8(Temp, _NAME); \
1294 _INFO.Date_From_Seconds_1904(Temp); \
1295 } \
1296 Param_Info1(_INFO); \
1297 } \
1298
1299//-------------------------------------------------------------------------
1300void File_Mpeg4::bloc()
1301{
1302 NAME_VERSION_FLAG("Base Location");
1303
1304 //Parsing
1305 Skip_XX(256, "baseLocation");
1306 Skip_XX(256, "purchaseLocation");
1307 Skip_XX(512, "Reserved");
1308}
1309
1310//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1311void File_Mpeg4::cdat()
1312{
1313 Element_Code=Element_Code==Elements::cdat?1:2;
1314
1315 if (!Status[IsAccepted])
1316 {
1317 Accept("EIA-608");
1318 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Format, "Final Cut EIA-608", Unlimited, true, true);
1319 }
1320 #ifdef MEDIAINFO_EIA608_YES
1321 if (Streams[(int32u)Element_Code].Parsers.empty())
1322 {
1323 File_Eia608* Parser=new File_Eia608();
1324 Open_Buffer_Init(Parser);
1325 Streams[(int32u)Element_Code].Parsers.push_back(Parser);
1326 }
1327 #endif //MEDIAINFO_EIA608_YES
1328
1329 Element_Name(Element_Code==1?"EIA-608-1":"EIA-608-2");
1330
1331 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1332 Demux(Buffer+Buffer_Offset, (size_t)Element_Size, ContentType_MainStream);
1333 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<Streams[(int32u)Element_Code].Parsers.size(); Pos++)
1334 {
1335 Streams[(int32u)Element_Code].Parsers[Pos]->FrameInfo.DTS=FrameInfo.DTS;
1336 Streams[(int32u)Element_Code].Parsers[Pos]->FrameInfo.DUR=FrameInfo.DUR/(Element_Size/2);
1337 }
1338 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1339 while (Element_Offset+2<=Element_Size)
1340 {
1341 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<Streams[(int32u)Element_Code].Parsers.size(); Pos++)
1342 Open_Buffer_Continue(Streams[(int32u)Element_Code].Parsers[Pos], Buffer+Buffer_Offset+(size_t)Element_Offset, 2);
1343 Element_Offset+=2;
1344 }
1345}
1346
1347//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1348void File_Mpeg4::free()
1349{
1350 Element_Name("Free space");
1351
1352 //Parsing
1353 #if MEDIAINFO_TRACE
1354 if (Trace_Activated)
1355 Param("Data", Ztring("(")+Ztring::ToZtring(Element_TotalSize_Get())+Ztring(" bytes)"));
1356 #endif //MEDIAINFO_TRACE
1357 #if MEDIAINFO_HASH
1358 if (!Hash || (!IsSecondPass && FirstMdatPos<FirstMoovPos))
1359 #endif //MEDIAINFO_HASH
1360 GoTo(File_Offset+Buffer_Offset+Element_TotalSize_Get()); //Not using Skip_XX() because we want to skip data we don't have, and Skip_XX() does a test on size of buffer
1361 #if MEDIAINFO_HASH
1362 else
1363 Element_Offset=Element_TotalSize_Get();
1364 #endif //MEDIAINFO_HASH
1365
1366 //ISM
1367 if (moof_traf_base_data_offset==(int64u)-1 && !data_offset_present)
1368 Stream->second.stco.push_back(File_Offset+Buffer_Offset);
1369}
1370
1371//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1372void File_Mpeg4::ftyp()
1373{
1374 Element_Name("File Type");
1375
1376 if (Count_Get(Stream_General))
1377 {
1378 Skip_XX(Element_Size, "Duplicate ftyp");
1379 return;
1380 }
1381
1382 //Parsing
1383 std::vector<int32u> ftyps;
1384 int32u MajorBrandVersion;
1385 Get_C4 (MajorBrand, "MajorBrand");
1386 ftyps.push_back(MajorBrand);
1387 Get_B4 (MajorBrandVersion, "MajorBrandVersion");
1388 while (Element_Offset<Element_Size)
1389 {
1390 int32u CompatibleBrand;
1391 Get_C4 (CompatibleBrand, "CompatibleBrand");
1392 ftyps.push_back(CompatibleBrand);
1393 }
1394
1395 FILLING_BEGIN();
1396 Accept("MPEG-4");
1397
1398 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Format, "MPEG-4");
1399 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<ftyps.size(); Pos++)
1400 switch (ftyps[Pos])
1401 {
1402 case Elements::ftyp_dash : if (Config->File_Names.size()==1)TestContinuousFileNames(1, __T("m4s")); break;
1403 case Elements::ftyp_caqv : Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Encoded_Application", "Casio Digital Camera"); break;
1404 default : ;
1405 }
1406 CodecID_Fill(Ztring().From_CC4(MajorBrand), Stream_General, 0, InfoCodecID_Format_Mpeg4);
1407 Ztring CodecID_String=Ztring().From_CC4(MajorBrand);
1408 if (MajorBrand==Elements::ftyp_qt)
1409 {
1410 ZtringList Version;
1411 Version.Separator_Set(0, __T("."));
1412 Version.push_back(Ztring().From_CC2(MajorBrandVersion>>16));
1413 Version.push_back(Ztring().From_CC1((int8u)(MajorBrandVersion>>8)));
1414 if (MajorBrandVersion&0xFF)
1415 Version.push_back(Ztring().From_CC1((int8u)MajorBrandVersion));
1416 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_CodecID_Version, Version.Read());
1417 CodecID_String += __T(' ');
1418 CodecID_String += Version.Read();
1419 }
1420 if (ftyps.size()>1)
1421 {
1422 ZtringList Compat;
1423 Compat.Separator_Set(0, __T("/"));
1424 for (size_t i=1; i<ftyps.size(); i++)
1425 if (ftyps[i])
1426 Compat.push_back(Ztring().From_CC4(ftyps[i]));
1427 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_CodecID_Compatible, Compat.Read());
1428 CodecID_String += __T(" (");
1429 CodecID_String += Compat.Read();
1430 CodecID_String += __T(')');
1431 }
1432 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_CodecID_String, CodecID_String, true);
1433 FILLING_END();
1434}
1435
1436//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1437void File_Mpeg4::idat()
1438{
1439 Element_Name("QTI");
1440
1441 //Parsing
1442 Skip_XX(Element_Size, "Data");
1443
1444 FILLING_BEGIN();
1445 Accept("QTI");
1446
1447 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Format, "MPEG-4");
1448 CodecID_Fill(__T("QTI"), Stream_General, 0, InfoCodecID_Format_Mpeg4);
1449 FILLING_END();
1450}
1451
1452//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1453void File_Mpeg4::idsc()
1454{
1455 Element_Name("QTI");
1456
1457 //Parsing
1458 Skip_XX(Element_Size, "Data");
1459
1460 FILLING_BEGIN();
1461 Accept("QTI");
1462
1463 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Format, "MPEG-4");
1464 CodecID_Fill(__T("QTI"), Stream_General, 0, InfoCodecID_Format_Mpeg4);
1465 FILLING_END();
1466}
1467
1468//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1469void File_Mpeg4::jp2c()
1470{
1471 Element_Name("JPEG 2000 content");
1472
1473 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_JPEG_YES)
1474 //Creating the parser
1475 File_Jpeg MI;
1476 if (IsSub || Config->File_Names.size()>1) //If contained in another container or several files, this is a video stream
1477 MI.StreamKind=Stream_Video;
1478 Open_Buffer_Init(&MI);
1479
1480 //Demux
1481 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1482 #if MEDIAINFO_EVENTS
1483 StreamIDs_Width[0]=0;
1484 #endif //MEDIAINFO_EVENTS
1485 if (Frame_Count_NotParsedIncluded==(int64u)-1)
1486 Frame_Count_NotParsedIncluded=0;
1487 if (Config->Demux_Rate_Get())
1488 {
1489 FrameInfo.DTS=float64_int64s(Frame_Count_NotParsedIncluded*1000000000/Config->Demux_Rate_Get());
1490 FrameInfo.PTS=FrameInfo.DTS;
1491 FrameInfo.DUR=float64_int64s(1000000000/Config->Demux_Rate_Get());
1492 }
1493 Demux(Buffer+Buffer_Offset, (size_t)Element_Size, ContentType_MainStream);
1494 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1495
1496 //Parsing
1497 Open_Buffer_Continue(&MI);
1498
1499 //Filling
1500 if (Frame_Count==0)
1501 {
1502 Accept("MPEG-4");
1503
1504 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Format, "JPEG 2000", Unlimited, true, true);
1505 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Format_Profile, "MPEG-4");
1506
1507 Finish(&MI);
1508 Merge(MI, MI.StreamKind, 0, 0);
1509
1510 Fill("MPEG-4");
1511 if (Config->File_Names.size()>1 && File_Size!=(int64u)-1)
1512 {
1513 int64u OverHead=Config->File_Sizes[0]-Element_Size;
1514 Fill(Stream_Video, 0, Video_StreamSize, File_Size-Config->File_Names.size()*OverHead, 10, true);
1515 }
1516 if (Config->ParseSpeed<1.0)
1517 Finish("MPEG-4");
1518 }
1519 Frame_Count++;
1520 if (Frame_Count_NotParsedIncluded!=(int64u)-1)
1521 Frame_Count_NotParsedIncluded++;
1522 #endif
1523
1524}
1525
1526//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1527void File_Mpeg4::jp2h()
1528{
1529 Element_Name("JPEG-2000 header");
1530}
1531
1532//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1533void File_Mpeg4::jp2h_colr()
1534{
1535 Element_Name("Color");
1536
1537 //Parsing
1538 int8u METH;
1539 Get_B1 (METH, "METH - Specification method"); Param_Info1(Mpeg4_jp2h_METH(METH));
1540 Skip_B1( "PREC - Precedence");
1541 Skip_B1( "APPROX - Colourspace approximation");
1542 switch (METH)
1543 {
1544 case 0x01 : {
1545 int32u EnumCS;
1546 Get_B4 (EnumCS, "EnumCS - Enumerated colourspace"); Param_Info1(Mpeg4_jp2h_EnumCS(EnumCS));
1547 Fill(StreamKind_Last, 0, "ColorSpace", Mpeg4_jp2h_EnumCS(EnumCS));
1548 }
1549 break;
1550 case 0x02 : Skip_XX(Element_Size-Element_Offset, "PROFILE");
1551 break;
1552 default : Skip_XX(Element_Size-Element_Offset, "Unknown");
1553 return;
1554 }
1555}
1556
1557//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1558void File_Mpeg4::jp2h_ihdr()
1559{
1560 Element_Name("Header");
1561
1562 //Parsing
1563 Skip_B4( "Height");
1564 Skip_B4( "Width");
1565 Skip_B2( "NC - Number of components");
1566 BS_Begin();
1567 Skip_SB( "BPC - Bits per component (Sign)");
1568 Skip_S1(7, "BPC - Bits per component (Value)");
1569 BS_End();
1570 Skip_B1( "C - Compression type");
1571 Skip_B1( "UnkC - Colourspace Unknown");
1572 Skip_B1( "IPR - Intellectual Property");
1573}
1574
1575//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1576void File_Mpeg4::mdat()
1577{
1578 #if MEDIAINFO_TRACE
1579 Trace_Layers_Update(8); //Streams
1580 #endif //MEDIAINFO_TRACE
1581
1582 if (!Status[IsAccepted])
1583 {
1584 Data_Accept("MPEG-4");
1585
1586 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Format, "QuickTime");
1587 }
1588 Element_Name("Data");
1589
1590 //Sizes
1591 if (Retrieve(Stream_General, 0, General_HeaderSize).empty())
1592 {
1593 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_HeaderSize, File_Offset+Buffer_Offset-Header_Size);
1594 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_DataSize, Element_TotalSize_Get()+Header_Size);
1595 if (File_Size!=(int64u)-1 && File_Offset+Buffer_Offset+Element_TotalSize_Get()<=File_Size)
1596 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_FooterSize, File_Size-(File_Offset+Buffer_Offset+Element_TotalSize_Get()));
1597 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_IsStreamable, FirstMoovPos==(int64u)-1?"No":"Yes");
1598 }
1599
1600 //Trace
1601 #if MEDIAINFO_TRACE
1602 Trace_Layers_Update(0); //Container1
1603 #endif //MEDIAINFO_TRACE
1604
1605 if (IsSecondPass && !mdat_Pos.empty() && mdat_Pos.begin()->Offset<File_Offset+Buffer_Offset+Element_TotalSize_Get())
1606 {
1607 //Next piece of data
1608 mdat_Pos_Temp=&mdat_Pos[0];
1609 IsParsing_mdat=true;
1610 mdat_StreamJump();
1611
1612 return; //Only if have something in this mdat
1613 }
1614
1615 //In case of mdat is before moov
1616 if (FirstMdatPos==(int64u)-1)
1617 {
1618 Buffer_Offset-=(size_t)Header_Size;
1619 Element_Level--;
1620 BookMark_Set(); //Remembering this place, for stream parsing in phase 2
1621 Element_Level++;
1622 Buffer_Offset+=(size_t)Header_Size;
1623
1624 FirstMdatPos=File_Offset+Buffer_Offset-Header_Size;
1625 }
1626 if (File_Offset+Buffer_Offset>LastMdatPos)
1627 LastMdatPos=File_Offset+Buffer_Offset+Element_TotalSize_Get();
1628
1629 //Parsing
1630 #if MEDIAINFO_TRACE
1631 if (Trace_Activated)
1632 Param("Data", Ztring("(")+Ztring::ToZtring(Element_TotalSize_Get())+Ztring(" bytes)"));
1633 #endif //MEDIAINFO_TRACE
1634 #if MEDIAINFO_HASH
1635 if (!Hash || (!IsSecondPass && FirstMdatPos<FirstMoovPos))
1636 #endif //MEDIAINFO_HASH
1637 GoTo(File_Offset+Buffer_Offset+Element_TotalSize_Get()); //Not using Skip_XX() because we want to skip data we don't have, and Skip_XX() does a test on size of buffer
1638 #if MEDIAINFO_HASH
1639 else
1640 Element_Offset=Element_TotalSize_Get();
1641 #endif //MEDIAINFO_HASH
1642
1643 //ISM
1644 if (moof_traf_base_data_offset==(int64u)-1 && !data_offset_present)
1645 Stream->second.stco.push_back(File_Offset+Buffer_Offset);
1646}
1647
1648//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1649void File_Mpeg4::mdat_xxxx()
1650{
1651 if (!Element_IsComplete_Get())
1652 {
1653 Element_WaitForMoreData();
1654 return;
1655 }
1656
1657 if (!IsSub)
1658 {
1659 if (Config->ParseSpeed>=1.0)
1660 Config->State_Set(((float)Buffer_TotalBytes)/File_Size);
1661 }
1662
1663 stream &Stream_Temp=Streams[(int32u)Element_Code];
1664 if (Stream_Temp.Parsers.empty())
1665 {
1666 Skip_XX(Element_Size, "Unknown");
1667 mdat_StreamJump();
1668 return;
1669 }
1670 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1671 if (Stream_Temp.StreamKind!=Stream_Other && Stream_Temp.StreamKind!=Stream_Max)
1672 {
1673 //DTS
1674 Frame_Count_NotParsedIncluded=Stream_Temp.stts_FramePos;
1675 if (Stream_Temp.stts_Durations_Pos<Stream_Temp.stts_Durations.size())
1676 {
1677 stream::stts_durations::iterator stts_Duration=Stream_Temp.stts_Durations.begin()+Stream_Temp.stts_Durations_Pos;
1678 int64u stts_Offset=stts_Duration->DTS_Begin+(((int64u)stts_Duration->SampleDuration)*(Frame_Count_NotParsedIncluded-stts_Duration->Pos_Begin));
1679 if (!Stream_Temp.edts.empty())
1680 {
1681 int64s Delay=0;
1682 switch (Stream_Temp.edts.size())
1683 {
1684 case 0 :
1685 break;
1686 case 1 :
1687 if (Stream_Temp.edts[0].Duration==Stream_Temp.tkhd_Duration && Stream_Temp.edts[0].Rate==0x00010000 && moov_mvhd_TimeScale)
1688 {
1689 Delay=-((int64s)Stream_Temp.edts[0].Delay);
1690 }
1691 break;
1692 case 2 :
1693 if (Stream_Temp.edts[0].Delay==(int32u)-1 && Stream_Temp.edts[0].Duration+Stream_Temp.edts[1].Duration==Stream_Temp.tkhd_Duration && Stream_Temp.edts[0].Rate==0x00010000 && Stream_Temp.edts[1].Rate==0x00010000 && moov_mvhd_TimeScale)
1694 {
1695 Delay=((int64s)Stream_Temp.edts[0].Duration)-Stream_Temp.edts[1].Delay;
1696 }
1697 break;
1698 default:
1699 break; //TODO: handle more complex Edit Lists
1700 }
1701
1702 if (-Delay<(int64s)stts_Offset)
1703 stts_Offset+=Delay;
1704 else
1705 stts_Offset=0;
1706 }
1707 FrameInfo.DTS=Stream_Temp.mdhd_TimeScale?(TimeCode_DtsOffset+stts_Offset*1000000000/Stream_Temp.mdhd_TimeScale):((int64u)-1);
1708 FrameInfo.PTS=Stream_Temp.PtsDtsAreSame?FrameInfo.DTS:(int64u)-1;
1709 FrameInfo.DUR=Stream_Temp.mdhd_TimeScale?(((int64u)stts_Duration->SampleDuration)*1000000000/Stream_Temp.mdhd_TimeScale):((int64u)-1);
1710 Stream_Temp.stts_FramePos++;
1711 if (Stream_Temp.stts_FramePos>=stts_Duration->Pos_End)
1712 Stream_Temp.stts_Durations_Pos++;
1713 if (!Stream_Temp.stss.empty())
1714 {
1715 Demux_random_access=false;
1716 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<Stream_Temp.stss.size(); Pos++)
1717 if (Stream_Temp.stss[Pos]==Frame_Count_NotParsedIncluded)
1718 {
1719 Demux_random_access=true;
1720 break;
1721 }
1722 }
1723 else
1724 Demux_random_access=true;
1725 }
1726 else
1727 {
1728 FrameInfo.DTS=(int64u)-1;
1729 FrameInfo.DUR=(int64u)-1;
1730 Stream_Temp.stts_FramePos++;
1731 }
1732
1733
1734 bool ShouldDemux=true;
1735 if (Stream_Temp.Demux_Level&(1<<7) && Element_Size-Stream_Temp.Demux_Offset)
1736 {
1737 if (Stream_Temp.Parsers[0]->Status[IsAccepted])
1738 ShouldDemux=false;
1739 else
1740 {
1741 //Checking if we need to add SPS/PPS
1742 size_t CheckMax=Stream_Temp.Demux_Offset+0x10; //SPS uses to be in the first bytes only
1743 if (CheckMax>Element_Size-4)
1744 CheckMax=Element_Size-4;
1745 ShouldDemux=false;
1746 for (size_t i=Stream_Temp.Demux_Offset; i<CheckMax; i++)
1747 if (Buffer[i]==0x00 && Buffer[i+1]==0x00 && Buffer[i+2]==0x01 && Buffer[i+3]==0x67)
1748 {
1749 Stream_Temp.Demux_Level&=~((1<<7)|(1<<6)); //Remove the flag, SPS/PPS detected
1750 ShouldDemux=true;
1751 break;
1752 }
1753 }
1754
1755 if (!ShouldDemux)
1756 {
1757 if (Stream_Temp.CodecID==0x4156696E) //AVin
1758 {
1759 int32u Height=Retrieve(Stream_Video, Stream_Temp.StreamPos, Video_Height).To_int32u();
1760 int32u Fields;
1761 if (Retrieve(Stream_Video, Stream_Temp.StreamPos, Video_ScanType)==__T("Progressive"))
1762 Fields=1;
1763 else if (Retrieve(Stream_Video, Stream_Temp.StreamPos, Video_ScanType)==__T("Interlaced"))
1764 Fields=2;
1765 else
1766 Fields=0;
1767 int32u SampleDuration;
1768 if (Stream_Temp.stts.size()==1)
1769 SampleDuration=Stream_Temp.stts[0].SampleDuration;
1770 else
1771 SampleDuration=0;
1772 Stream_Temp.CodecID=File_Avc::AVC_Intra_CodecID_FromMeta(Height, Fields, SampleDuration, Stream_Temp.mdhd_TimeScale, Stream_Temp.stsz_Sample_Size);
1773 }
1774
1775 //Stream_Temp.Demux_Level|= (1<<6); //In case of seek, we need to send again SPS/PPS //Deactivated because Hydra does not decode after a seek + 1 SPS/PPS only.
1776 //Stream_Temp.Demux_Level&=~(1<<7); //Remove the flag, SPS/PPS sent
1777 Demux_Level=Stream_Temp.Demux_Level;
1778 File_Avc::avcintra_header AvcIntraHeader=File_Avc::AVC_Intra_Headers_Data(Stream_Temp.CodecID);
1779 size_t Buffer_Temp_Size=AvcIntraHeader.Size+(size_t)(Element_Size-Stream_Temp.Demux_Offset);
1780 int8u* Buffer_Temp_Data=new int8u[Buffer_Temp_Size];
1781 if (AvcIntraHeader.Data)
1782 memcpy(Buffer_Temp_Data, AvcIntraHeader.Data, AvcIntraHeader.Size);
1783 memcpy(Buffer_Temp_Data+AvcIntraHeader.Size, Buffer+Buffer_Offset+Stream_Temp.Demux_Offset, (size_t)(Element_Size-Stream_Temp.Demux_Offset));
1784 Demux(Buffer_Temp_Data, Buffer_Temp_Size, ContentType_MainStream);
1785 Open_Buffer_Continue(Stream_Temp.Parsers[0], AvcIntraHeader.Data, AvcIntraHeader.Size);
1786 ShouldDemux = false;
1787 }
1788 }
1789 if (ShouldDemux)
1790 {
1791 Demux_Level=Stream_Temp.Demux_Level;
1792 Demux(Buffer+Buffer_Offset+Stream_Temp.Demux_Offset, (size_t)(Element_Size-Stream_Temp.Demux_Offset), ContentType_MainStream);
1793 }
1794 }
1795 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1796
1797 for (size_t Pos=0; Pos<Stream_Temp.Parsers.size(); Pos++)
1798 {
1799 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1800 Stream_Temp.Parsers[Pos]->FrameInfo=FrameInfo;
1801 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1802
1803 Open_Buffer_Continue(Stream_Temp.Parsers[Pos], Buffer+Buffer_Offset, (size_t)Element_Size);
1804 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1805 if (Config->Demux_EventWasSent && Config->Demux_Unpacketize_Get())
1806 Stream_Temp.Demux_EventWasSent=true;
1807 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1808 Element_Show();
1809
1810 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1811 if (!Stream_Temp.IsFilled && Stream_Temp.Parsers[Pos]->Status[IsFilled])
1812 {
1813 if (Stream_Temp.StreamKind==Stream_Other) //If this is a TimeCode track
1814 {
1815 if (((File_Mpeg4_TimeCode*)Stream_Temp.Parsers[Pos])->Pos!=(int32u)-1)
1816 {
1817 for (std::map<int32u, stream>::iterator StreamTemp=Streams.begin(); StreamTemp!=Streams.end(); ++StreamTemp)
1818 if (StreamTemp->second.TimeCode_TrackID==(int32u)Element_Code)
1819 {
1820 TimeCode_FrameOffset=((File_Mpeg4_TimeCode*)Stream_Temp.Parsers[Pos])->Pos;
1821 TimeCode_DtsOffset=float64_int64s(((float64)TimeCode_FrameOffset)*1000000000*Stream_Temp.TimeCode->FrameDuration/Stream_Temp.TimeCode->TimeScale);
1822 }
1823 }
1824 }
1825
1826 Stream_Temp.IsFilled=true;
1827
1828 if (Config->ParseSpeed<1 && !mdat_Pos.empty())
1829 {
1830 bool File_Offset_Next_IsValid;
1831 int64u File_Offset_Next;
1832 if (mdat_Pos_Temp!=mdat_Pos_Max)
1833 {
1834 File_Offset_Next=mdat_Pos_Temp->Offset;
1835 File_Offset_Next_IsValid=true;
1836 }
1837 else
1838 {
1839 File_Offset_Next=(int64u)-1;
1840 File_Offset_Next_IsValid=false;
1841 }
1842 mdat_pos mdat_Pos_New;
1843 mdat_Pos_Max=mdat_Pos.empty()?NULL:(&mdat_Pos[0]+mdat_Pos.size());
1844 if (!mdat_Pos.empty())
1845 {
1846 for (mdat_Pos_Type* mdat_Pos_Item=&mdat_Pos[0]; mdat_Pos_Item<mdat_Pos_Max; ++mdat_Pos_Item)
1847 if (mdat_Pos_Item->StreamID!=(int32u)Element_Code)
1848 mdat_Pos_New.push_back(*mdat_Pos_Item);
1849 }
1850 mdat_Pos=mdat_Pos_New;
1851 std::sort(mdat_Pos.begin(), mdat_Pos.end(), &mdat_pos_sort);
1852 mdat_Pos_Temp=mdat_Pos.empty()?NULL:&mdat_Pos[0];
1853 mdat_Pos_Max=mdat_Pos_Temp+mdat_Pos.size();
1854 if (File_Offset_Next_IsValid)
1855 for (; mdat_Pos_Temp<mdat_Pos_Max; ++mdat_Pos_Temp)
1856 {
1857 if (mdat_Pos_Temp->Offset>=File_Offset_Next)
1858 break;
1859 }
1860 else
1861 mdat_Pos_Temp=mdat_Pos_Max;
1862 }
1863 }
1864 #endif //MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1865
1866 //Multiple parsers
1867 if (Stream_Temp.Parsers.size()>1)
1868 {
1869 if (!Stream_Temp.Parsers[Pos]->Status[IsAccepted] && Stream_Temp.Parsers[Pos]->Status[IsFinished])
1870 {
1871 delete *(Stream_Temp.Parsers.begin()+Pos);
1872 Stream_Temp.Parsers.erase(Stream_Temp.Parsers.begin()+Pos);
1873 Pos--;
1874 }
1875 else if (Stream_Temp.Parsers.size()>1 && Stream_Temp.Parsers[Pos]->Status[IsAccepted])
1876 {
1877 File__Analyze* Parser=Stream_Temp.Parsers[Pos];
1878 for (size_t Pos2=0; Pos2<Stream_Temp.Parsers.size(); Pos2++)
1879 {
1880 if (Pos2!=Pos)
1881 delete *(Stream_Temp.Parsers.begin()+Pos2);
1882 }
1883 Stream_Temp.Parsers.clear();
1884 Stream_Temp.Parsers.push_back(Parser);
1885 }
1886 }
1887 }
1888
1889 //Next piece of data
1890 Element_Offset=Element_Size;
1891 Element_Show();
1892 mdat_StreamJump();
1893}
1894
1895//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1896void File_Mpeg4::mdat_StreamJump()
1897{
1898 //Finding right file offset
1899 int64u ToJump=File_Size;
1900 if (!mdat_Pos.empty() && mdat_Pos_Temp!=mdat_Pos_Max)
1901 {
1902 ToJump=mdat_Pos_Temp->Offset;
1903 #if MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1904 if (Config->ParseSpeed==1)
1905 {
1906 std::map<int64u, int64u>::iterator StreamOffset_Jump_Temp=StreamOffset_Jump.find(ToJump);
1907 if (StreamOffset_Jump_Temp!=StreamOffset_Jump.end())
1908 {
1909 ToJump=StreamOffset_Jump_Temp->second;
1910 if (!mdat_Pos.empty())
1911 {
1912 mdat_Pos_Temp=&mdat_Pos[0];
1913 while (mdat_Pos_Temp<mdat_Pos_Max && mdat_Pos_Temp->Offset!=ToJump)
1914 mdat_Pos_Temp++;
1915 }
1916 else
1917 mdat_Pos_Temp=NULL;
1918 }
1919 }
1920 #endif // MEDIAINFO_DEMUX
1921 }
1922 if (ToJump>File_Size)
1923 ToJump=File_Size;
1924 if (ToJump!=File_Offset+Buffer_Offset+Element_Size)
1925 {
1926 if (!Status[IsAccepted])
1927 Data_Accept("MPEG-4");
1928 #if MEDIAINFO_HASH
1929 if (Config->File_Hash_Get().to_ulong() && ((IsSecondPass && mdat_Pos_NormalParsing) || FirstMoovPos<FirstMdatPos))
1930 Hash_ParseUpTo=ToJump;
1931 else
1932 #endif //MEDIAINFO_HASH
1933 Data_GoTo(ToJump, "MPEG-4"); //Not just after
1934 }
1935}

1938void File_Mpeg4::mfra()
1939{
1940 Element_Name("Movie Fragment Random Access");
1941}
1942
1943//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1944void File_Mpeg4::mfra_mfro()
1945{
1946 NAME_VERSION_FLAG("Movie Fragment Random Access Offset");
1947
1948 //Parsing
1949 Skip_B4( "size");
1950}
1951
1952//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
1953void File_Mpeg4::mfra_tfra()
1954{
1955 NAME_VERSION_FLAG("Track Fragment Random Access");
1956
1957 //Parsing
1958 int32u number_of_entry;
1959 int8u length_size_of_traf_num, length_size_of_trun_num, length_size_of_sample_num;
1960 Skip_B4( "track_ID");
1961 BS_Begin();
1962 Skip_S1(26, "reserved");
1963 Get_S1 (2, length_size_of_traf_num, "length_size_of_traf_num");
1964 Get_S1 (2, length_size_of_trun_num, "length_size_of_trun_num");
1965 Get_S1 (2, length_size_of_sample_num, "length_size_of_sample_num");
1966 BS_End();
1967 Get_B4(number_of_entry, "number_of_entry");
1968 for(int32u Pos=0; Pos<number_of_entry; Pos++)
1969 {
1970 Element_Begin1("entry");
1971 int64u time, moof_offset;
1972 Get_B_DEPENDOFVERSION(time, "time");
1973 Get_B_DEPENDOFVERSION(moof_offset, "moof_offset");
1974 switch (length_size_of_traf_num)
1975 {
1976 case 0 : Skip_B1( "traf_number"); break;
1977 case 1 : Skip_B2( "traf_number"); break;
1978 case 2 : Skip_B3( "traf_number"); break;
1979 case 3 : Skip_B4( "traf_number"); break;
1980 default: ;
1981 }
1982 switch (length_size_of_trun_num)
1983 {
1984 case 0 : Skip_B1( "trun_num"); break;
1985 case 1 : Skip_B2( "trun_num"); break;
1986 case 2 : Skip_B3( "trun_num"); break;
1987 case 3 : Skip_B4( "trun_num"); break;
1988 default: ;
1989 }
1990 switch (length_size_of_sample_num)
1991 {
1992 case 0 : Skip_B1( "sample_num"); break;
1993 case 1 : Skip_B2( "sample_num"); break;
1994 case 2 : Skip_B3( "sample_num"); break;
1995 case 3 : Skip_B4( "sample_num"); break;
1996 default: ;
1997 }
1998 Element_End0();
1999 }
2000}
2001
2002//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
2003void File_Mpeg4::moof()
2004{
2005 Element_Name("Movie Fragment");
2006
2007 if (IsSecondPass)
2008 {
2009 #if MEDIAINFO_TRACE
2010 if (Trace_Activated)
2011 Param("Data", Ztring("(")+Ztring::ToZtring(Element_TotalSize_Get())+Ztring(" bytes)"));
2012 #endif //MEDIAINFO_TRACE
2013 #if MEDIAINFO_HASH
2014 if (!Hash || (!IsSecondPass && FirstMdatPos<FirstMoovPos))
2015 #endif //MEDIAINFO_HASH
2016 GoTo(File_Offset+Buffer_Offset+Element_TotalSize_Get()); //Not using Skip_XX() because we want to skip data we don't have, and Skip_XX() does a test on size of buffer
2017 #if MEDIAINFO_HASH
2018 else
2019 Element_Offset=Element_TotalSize_Get();
2020 #endif //MEDIAINFO_HASH
2021 return;
2022 }
2023
2024 IsFragmented=true;
2025 moof_base_data_offset=File_Offset+Buffer_Offset-Header_Size;
2026 data_offset_present=true;
2027}
2028
2029//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
2030void File_Mpeg4::moof_mfhd()
2031{
2032 NAME_VERSION_FLAG("Movie Fragment Header");
2033
2034 //Parsing
2035 Skip_B4( "sequence_number");
2036}
2037
2038//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
2039void File_Mpeg4::moof_traf()
2040{
2041 Element_Name("Track Fragment");
2042
2043 //Filling
2044 moof_traf_base_data_offset=(int64u)-1;
2045 if (Streams.empty())
2046 Streams[(int32u)-1]; //Creating a virtual track in case there is no track
2047 Stream=Streams.begin(); //Using first track in case there is no track header
2048 moof_traf_default_sample_duration=Stream->second.mvex_trex_default_sample_duration;
2049 moof_traf_default_sample_size=Stream->second.mvex_trex_default_sample_size;
2050}
2051
2052//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
2053void File_Mpeg4::moof_traf_sdtp()
2054{
2055 NAME_VERSION_FLAG("Independent and Disposable Samples");
2056
2057 //Parsing
2058 //for (int32u Pos=0; Pos<sample_count; Pos++) //sample_count should be taken from stsz or stz2
2059 while (Element_Offset<Element_Size)
2060 {
2061 Element_Begin1("sample");
2062 BS_Begin();
2063 Skip_S1(2, "reserved");
2064 Info_S1(2, sample_depends_on, "sample_depends_on"); Param_Info1(Mpeg4_sample_depends_on[sample_depends_on]);
2065 Info_S1(2, sample_is_depended_on, "sample_is_depended_on"); Param_Info1(Mpeg4_sample_is_depended_on[sample_is_depended_on]);
2066 Info_S1(2, sample_has_redundancy, "sample_has_redundancy"); Param_Info1(Mpeg4_sample_has_redundancy[sample_has_redundancy]);
2067 BS_End();
2068 Element_End0();
2069 }
2070}
2071
2072//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
2073void File_Mpeg4::moof_traf_tfhd()
2074{
2075 NAME_VERSION_FLAG("Track Fragment Header");
2076
2077 //Parsing
2078 bool base_data_offset_present, sample_description_index_present, default_sample_duration_present, default_sample_size_present, default_sample_flags_present;
2079 Get_Flags (Flags, 0, base_data_offset_present, "base-data-offset-present");
2080 Get_Flags (Flags, 1, sample_description_index_present, "sample-description-index-present");
2081 Get_Flags (Flags, 3, default_sample_duration_present, "default-sample-duration-present");
2082 Get_Flags (Flags, 4, default_sample_size_present, "default-sample-size-present");
2083 Get_Flags (Flags, 5, default_sample_flags_present, "default-sample-flags-present");
2084 Skip_Flags(Flags, 16, "duration-is-empty");
2085 Get_B4 (moov_trak_tkhd_TrackID, "track_ID");
2086 if (base_data_offset_present)
2087 Get_B8 (moof_traf_base_data_offset, "base_data_offset");
2088 if (sample_description_index_present)
2089 Skip_B4( "sample_description_index");
2090 if (default_sample_duration_present)
2091 Get_B4 (moof_traf_default_sample_duration, "default_sample_duration");
2092 if (default_sample_size_present)
2093 Get_B4 (moof_traf_default_sample_size, "default_sample_size");
2094 if (default_sample_flags_present)
2095 Skip_B4( "default_sample_flags");
2096
2097 FILLING_BEGIN();
2098 Stream=Streams.find(moov_trak_tkhd_TrackID);
2099 if (Stream==Streams.end())
2100 Stream=Streams.begin();
2101 if (!default_sample_duration_present)
2102 moof_traf_default_sample_duration=Stream->second.mvex_trex_default_sample_duration;
2103 if (!default_sample_size_present)
2104 moof_traf_default_sample_size=Stream->second.mvex_trex_default_sample_size;
2105 FILLING_END();
2106}
2107
2108//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
2109void File_Mpeg4::moof_traf_trun()
2110{
2111 NAME_VERSION_FLAG("Track Fragment Run");
2112
2113 //Parsing
2114 int32u sample_count;
2115 bool first_sample_flags_present, sample_duration_present, sample_size_present, sample_flags_present, sample_composition_time_offset_present;
2116 Get_Flags (Flags, 0, data_offset_present, "data-offset-present");
2117 Get_Flags (Flags, 2, first_sample_flags_present, "first-sample-flags-present");
2118 Get_Flags (Flags, 8, sample_duration_present, "sample-duration-present");
2119 Get_Flags (Flags, 9, sample_size_present, "sample-size-present");
2120 Get_Flags (Flags, 10, sample_flags_present, "sample-flags-present");
2121 Get_Flags (Flags, 11, sample_composition_time_offset_present, "sample-composition-time-offsets-present");
2122 Get_B4 (sample_count, "sample_count");
2123 int64u data_offset_Final=moof_traf_base_data_offset!=(int64u)-1?moof_traf_base_data_offset:moof_base_data_offset;
2124 if (data_offset_present)
2125 {
2126 int32u data_offset;
2127 Get_B4 (data_offset, "data_offset");
2128 data_offset_Final+=data_offset;
2129 }
2130
2131 //Filling
2132 if (moof_traf_base_data_offset!=(int64u)-1 || data_offset_present)
2133 Stream->second.stco.push_back(data_offset_Final);
2134 stream::stsc_struct Stsc;
2135 if (Stream->second.stsc.empty())
2136 Stsc.FirstChunk=1;
2137 else
2138 Stsc.FirstChunk=Stream->second.stsc[Stream->second.stsc.size()-1].FirstChunk+1;
2139 Stsc.SamplesPerChunk=sample_count;
2140 Stream->second.stsc.push_back(Stsc);
2141 if (!sample_duration_present)
2142 moov_trak_mdia_minf_stbl_stts_Common(sample_count, moof_traf_default_sample_duration);
2143 if (!sample_size_present)
2144 Stream->second.stsz.resize(Stream->second.stsz.size()+sample_count, moof_traf_default_sample_size);
2145
2146 if (first_sample_flags_present)
2147 Skip_B4( "first_sample_flags");
2148 for (int32u Pos=0; Pos<sample_count; Pos++)
2149 {
2150 Element_Begin1("sample");
2151 if (sample_duration_present)
2152 {
2153 int32u sample_duration;
2154 Get_B4 (sample_duration, "sample_duration");
2155
2156 moov_trak_mdia_minf_stbl_stts_Common(1, sample_duration);
2157 }
2158 if (sample_size_present)
2159 {
2160 int32u sample_size;
2161 Get_B4 (sample_size, "sample_size");
2162
2163 //Filling
2164 Stream->second.stsz_StreamSize+=sample_size;
2165 Stream->second.stsz_Total.push_back(sample_size);
2166 if (Stream->second.stsz.size()<FrameCount_MaxPerStream)
2167 Stream->second.stsz.push_back(sample_size);
2168 }
2169 if (sample_flags_present)
2170 Skip_B4( "sample_flags");
2171 if (sample_composition_time_offset_present)
2172 Skip_B4( "sample_composition_time_offset");
2173 Element_End0();
2174 }
2175}
2176
2177//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
2178void File_Mpeg4::moov()
2179{
2180 if (!Status[IsAccepted])
2181 {
2182 Data_Accept("MPEG-4");
2183
2184 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Format, "QuickTime"); //If there is no ftyp atom, this is an old Quictime file
2185 }
2186 Element_Name("File header");
2187
2188 if (IsSecondPass || FirstMoovPos!=(int64u)-1) //Currently, the 1 moov atom is used
2189 {
2190 #if MEDIAINFO_TRACE
2191 if (Trace_Activated)
2192 Param("Data", Ztring("(")+Ztring::ToZtring(Element_TotalSize_Get())+Ztring(" bytes)"));
2193 #endif //MEDIAINFO_TRACE
2194 #if MEDIAINFO_HASH
2195 if (!Hash || (!IsSecondPass && FirstMdatPos<FirstMoovPos))
2196 #endif //MEDIAINFO_HASH
2197 GoTo(File_Offset+Buffer_Offset+Element_TotalSize_Get()); //Not using Skip_XX() because we want to skip data we don't have, and Skip_XX() does a test on size of buffer
2198 #if MEDIAINFO_HASH
2199 else
2200 Element_Offset=Element_TotalSize_Get();
2201 #endif //MEDIAINFO_HASH
2202 return;
2203 }
2204
2205 if (FirstMoovPos==(int64u)-1)
2206 FirstMoovPos=File_Offset+Buffer_Offset-Header_Size;
2207 /*
2208 else
2209 {
2210 //In case of more than 1 moov atom, the last one is used (previous ones are trashed)
2211 Streams.clear();
2212 for (size_t StreamKind=Stream_General+1; StreamKind<Stream_Max; StreamKind++)
2213 while (Count_Get((stream_t)StreamKind))
2214 Stream_Erase((stream_t)StreamKind, Count_Get((stream_t)StreamKind)-1);
2215 }
2216 */
2217}

2235//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
2236void File_Mpeg4::moov_cmov_cmvd()
2237{
2238 Element_Name("Data");
2239
2240 switch (moov_cmov_dcom_Compressor)
2241 {
2242 case Elements::moov_cmov_dcom_zlib : moov_cmov_cmvd_zlib(); break;
2243 default: Skip_XX(Element_Size, "Data");
2244 }
2245}
2246
2247//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
2248void File_Mpeg4::moov_cmov_cmvd_zlib()
2249{
2250 Element_Name("Zlib");
2251
2252 //Parsing
2253 int32u Dest_Size32;
2254 Get_B4(Dest_Size32, "Destination size");
2255
2256 FILLING_BEGIN();
2257 //Sizes
2258 unsigned long Source_Size=(unsigned long)(Element_Size-Element_Offset);
2259 unsigned long Dest_Size=Dest_Size32;
2260
2261 //Uncompressing
2262 int8u* Dest=new int8u[Dest_Size];
2263 if (uncompress((Bytef*)Dest, &Dest_Size, (const Bytef*)Buffer+Buffer_Offset+4, Source_Size)<0)
2264 {
2265 Skip_XX(Element_Size, "Problem during the decompression");
2266 delete[] Dest; //Dest=NULL;
2267 return;
2268 }
2269
2270 //Exiting this element
2271 Skip_XX(Element_Size-Element_Offset, "Will be parsed");
2272
2273 //Configuring level
2274 std::vector<int64u> Element_Sizes_Sav;
2275 size_t Element_Level_Sav=Element_Level;
2276 while(Element_Level)
2277 {
2278 Element_Sizes_Sav.push_back(Element_TotalSize_Get());
2279 Element_End0();
2280 }
2281
2282 //Configuring buffer
2283 const int8u* Buffer_Sav=Buffer;
2284 size_t Buffer_Size_Sav=Buffer_Size;
2285 int8u* Buffer_Temp_Sav=Buffer_Temp;
2286 size_t Buffer_Temp_Size_Sav=Buffer_Temp_Size;
2287 size_t Buffer_Offset_Sav=Buffer_Offset;
2288 size_t Buffer_Offset_Temp_Sav=Buffer_Offset_Temp;
2289 Buffer=NULL;
2290 Buffer_Size=0;
2291 Buffer_Temp=NULL;
2292 Buffer_Temp_Size=0;
2293 Buffer_Offset=0;
2294 Buffer_Offset_Temp=0;
2295
2296 //Configuring file size
2297 int64u File_Offset_Sav=File_Offset;
2298 int64u File_Size_Sav=File_Size;
2299 if (File_Size<File_Offset+Buffer_Offset+Element_Offset+Dest_Size)
2300 File_Size=File_Offset+Buffer_Offset+Element_Offset+Dest_Size;
2301 Element_Level++;
2302 Header_Fill_Size(File_Size);
2303 Element_Level--;
2304
2305 //Configuring some status info
2306 FirstMoovPos=(int64u)-1;
2307
2308 //Parsing
2309 Buffer=Dest;
2310 Buffer_Size=Dest_Size;
2311 while (Open_Buffer_Continue_Loop());
2312 delete[] Dest; //Dest=NULL;
2313
2314 //Resetting file info
2315 File_Offset=File_Offset_Sav;
2316 File_Size=File_Size_Sav;
2317
2318 //Resetting buffer
2319 Buffer=Buffer_Sav;
2320 Buffer_Size=Buffer_Size_Sav;
2321 Buffer_Temp=Buffer_Temp_Sav;
2322 Buffer_Temp_Size=Buffer_Temp_Size_Sav;
2323 Buffer_Offset=Buffer_Offset_Sav;
2324 Buffer_Offset_Temp=Buffer_Offset_Temp_Sav;
2325
2326 //Configuring level
2327 while(Element_Level)
2328 Element_End0();
2329 Element_Level++;
2330 Header_Fill_Size(File_Size-(File_Offset+Buffer_Offset));
2331 Element_Level--;
2332 while(Element_Level<Element_Level_Sav)
2333 {
2334 Element_Begin1(__T("...Continued")); //TODO: better method
2335 Element_Begin1(__T("...Continued"));
2336 Header_Fill_Size(Element_Sizes_Sav[0]);
2337 Element_End0();
2338 }
2339
2340 //Filling
2341 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Format_Settings, "Compressed header");
2342 FILLING_END();
2343}

2464
2465//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
2466void File_Mpeg4::moov_meta_ilst_xxxx_data()
2467{
2468 Element_Name("Data");
2469
2470 //Parsing
2471 int32u Kind, Language;
2472 Ztring Value;
2473 Get_B4(Kind, "Kind"); Param_Info1(Mpeg4_Meta_Kind(Kind));
2474
2475 //Error detection
2476 switch (Element_Code_Get(Element_Level-1))
2477 {
2478 case Elements::moov_meta__disk :
2479 case Elements::moov_meta__trkn :
2480 if (Kind)
2481 {
2482 //Not normal
2483 Kind=0x00;
2484 }
2485 default : ;
2486 }
2487
2488 switch (Kind)
2489 {
2490 case 0x00 : //Binary
2491 Get_B4(Language, "Language");
2492 switch (Element_Code_Get(Element_Level-1))
2493 {
2494 case Elements::moov_meta__disk :
2495 {
2496 //Parsing
2497 int16u Position, Total;
2498 Skip_B2( "Reserved");
2499 Get_B2(Position, "Position");
2500 Get_B2(Total, "Total");
2501 if (Element_Offset+2<=Element_Size)
2502 Skip_B2( "Reserved"); //Sometimes there are 2 more bytes, unknown
2503
2504 //Filling
2505 if (Position)
2506 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Part_Position, Position, 10, true);
2507 if (Total)
2508 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Part_Position_Total, Total, 10, true);
2509 }
2510 return;
2511 case Elements::moov_meta__trkn :
2512 {
2513 //Parsing
2514 int16u Position, Total;
2515 Skip_B2( "Reserved");
2516 Get_B2(Position, "Position");
2517 Get_B2(Total, "Total");
2518 if (Element_Offset+2<=Element_Size)
2519 Skip_B2( "Reserved"); //Sometimes there are 2 more bytes, unknown
2520
2521 //Filling
2522 if (Position)
2523 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Track_Position, Position, 10, true);
2524 if (Total)
2525 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Track_Position_Total, Total, 10, true);
2526 }
2527 return;
2528 case Elements::moov_meta__covr :
2529 {
2530 std::string Data_Raw((const char*)(Buffer+(size_t)(Buffer_Offset+Element_Offset)), (size_t)(Element_Size-Element_Offset));
2531 std::string Data_Base64(Base64::encode(Data_Raw));
2532 Skip_XX(Element_Size-Element_Offset, "Data");
2533
2534 //Filling
2535 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Cover_Data, Data_Base64);
2536 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Cover, "Yes");
2537 }
2538 return;
2539 case Elements::moov_meta__gnre :
2540 {
2541 if (Element_Size-Element_Offset==2)
2542 {
2543 int16u Genre;
2544 Get_B2(Genre, "Genre");
2545
2546 //Filling
2547 if (Genre)
2548 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Genre, Genre-1);
2549 }
2550 else
2551 Skip_XX(Element_Size-Element_Offset,"Data");
2552 }
2553 return;
2554 default:
2555 Skip_XX(Element_Size-Element_Offset,"To decode!");
2556 Value=__T("(Binary)");
2557 }
2558 break;
2559 case 0x01 : //UTF-8
2560 Get_B4(Language, "Language");
2561 switch (Element_Code_Get(Element_Level-1))
2562 {
2563 case Elements::moov_meta___day :
2564 {
2565 std::string ValueS;
2566 Get_String(Element_Size-Element_Offset, ValueS, "Value");
2567 Value.Date_From_String(ValueS.c_str(), ValueS.size());
2568 }
2569 break;
2570 default:
2571 Get_UTF8(Element_Size-Element_Offset, Value, "Value");
2572 }
2573 break;
2574 case 0x02 : //UTF-16
2575 Value=__T("UTF-16 encoding not yet supported");
2576 break;
2577 case 0x03 : //Mac String
2578 Get_B4(Language, "Language"); //To confirm
2579 Get_Local(Element_Size-Element_Offset, Value, "Value");
2580 break;
2581 case 0x0D : //JPEG
2582 Get_B4(Language, "Language");
2583 switch (Element_Code_Get(Element_Level-1))
2584 {
2585 case Elements::moov_meta__covr :
2586 {
2587 std::string Data_Raw((const char*)(Buffer+(size_t)(Buffer_Offset+Element_Offset)), (size_t)(Element_Size-Element_Offset));
2588 std::string Data_Base64(Base64::encode(Data_Raw));
2589 Skip_XX(Element_Size-Element_Offset, "Data");
2590
2591 //Filling
2592 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Cover_Data, Data_Base64);
2593 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Cover, "Yes");
2594 }
2595 return;
2596 default:
2597 Value=__T("(Binary)");
2598 }
2599 break;
2600 case 0x0E : //PNG
2601 Get_B4(Language, "Language");
2602 switch (Element_Code_Get(Element_Level-1))
2603 {
2604 case Elements::moov_meta__covr :
2605 {
2606 std::string Data_Raw((const char*)(Buffer+(size_t)(Buffer_Offset+Element_Offset)), (size_t)(Element_Size-Element_Offset));
2607 std::string Data_Base64(Base64::encode(Data_Raw));
2608 Skip_XX(Element_Size-Element_Offset, "Data");
2609
2610 //Filling
2611 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Cover_Data, Data_Base64);
2612 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Cover, "Yes");
2613 }
2614 return;
2615 default:
2616 Value=__T("(Binary)");
2617 }
2618 break;
2619 case 0x15 : //Signed Integer
2620 {
2621 Get_B4(Language, "Language");
2622 switch (Element_Size-Element_Offset)
2623 {
2624 case 1 : {int8u ValueI; Get_B1(ValueI, "Value"); Value.From_Number((int8s) ValueI);}; break;
2625 case 2 : {int16u ValueI; Get_B2(ValueI, "Value"); Value.From_Number((int16s)ValueI);}; break;
2626 case 4 : {int32u ValueI; Get_B4(ValueI, "Value"); Value.From_Number((int32s)ValueI);}; break;
2627 case 8 : {int64u ValueI; Get_B8(ValueI, "Value"); Value.From_Number((int64s)ValueI);}; break;
2628 default : Value=__T("Unknown kind of integer value!");
2629 }
2630 }
2631 break;
2632 case 0x16 : //Float 32
2633 Skip_XX(4, "To decode!");
2634 //Value=__T("Float32 encoding not yet supported");
2635 break;
2636 case 0x17 : //Float 64
2637 Skip_XX(8, "To decode!");
2638 //Value=__T("Float64 encoding not yet supported");
2639 break;
2640 default: Value=__T("Unknown kind of value!");
2641 }
2642
2643 switch (moov_meta_hdlr_Type)
2644 {
2645 case Elements::moov_meta_hdlr_mdir :
2646 {
2647 FILLING_BEGIN();
2648 std::string Parameter;
2649 if (Element_Code_Get(Element_Level-1)==Elements::moov_meta______)
2650 {
2651 if (moov_meta_ilst_xxxx_name_Name=="iTunMOVI" && Element_Size>8)
2652 {
2653 #if defined(MEDIAINFO_PROPERTYLIST_YES)
2654 File_PropertyList MI;
2655 Open_Buffer_Init(&MI);
2656 Open_Buffer_Continue(&MI, Buffer+Buffer_Offset+8, (size_t)(Element_Size-8));
2657 Open_Buffer_Finalize(&MI);
2658 Merge(MI, Stream_General, 0, 0);
2659 #endif //defined(MEDIAINFO_PROPERTYLIST_YES)
2660 }
2661 else
2662 Metadata_Get(Parameter, moov_meta_ilst_xxxx_name_Name);
2663 }
2664 else
2665 Metadata_Get(Parameter, Element_Code_Get(Element_Level-1));
2666 if (Parameter=="Encoded_Application")
2667 {
2668 if (Value.find(__T("Nero AAC codec"))==0)
2669 {
2670 ZtringList List; List.Separator_Set(0, __T(" / "));
2671 List.Write(Value);
2672 Element_Info1(Parameter.c_str());
2673 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Encoded_Library_Name, List(0), true);
2674 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Encoded_Library_Version, List(1), true);
2675 Parameter.clear(); //Set as already filled
2676 }
2677 }
2678 if (Parameter=="cdec")
2679 {
2680 if (Value.find(__T("ndaudio "))==0)
2681 {
2682 ZtringList List; List.Separator_Set(0, __T(" / "));
2683 List.Write(Value);
2684 Element_Info1(Parameter.c_str());
2685 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Encoded_Library_Name, "Nero AAC codec", Unlimited, true, true);
2686 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Encoded_Library_Name, List(0).substr(8, string::npos), true);
2687 Fill(Stream_Audio, StreamPos_Last, Audio_Encoded_Library_Settings, List(1), true);
2688 Parameter.clear(); //Set as already filled
2689 }
2690 }
2691 if (Parameter=="Compilation" || Parameter=="HDVideo" || Parameter=="iTunesU" || Parameter=="Podcast")
2692 {
2693 if (Value==__T("1"))
2694 Value=__T("Yes");
2695 else
2696 Value.clear(); //This is usually set to 0 even if the user did not explicitely indicated something (default)
2697 }
2698 if (Parameter=="BPM")
2699 {
2700 if (Value==__T("0"))
2701 Value.clear();
2702 }
2703 if (Parameter=="ContentType")
2704 {
2705 if (Value==__T("0")) Value=__T("Movie");
2706 else if (Value==__T("1")) Value=__T("Music");
2707 else if (Value==__T("2")) Value=__T("Audiobook");
2708 else if (Value==__T("5")) Value=__T("Whacked Bookmark");
2709 else if (Value==__T("6")) Value=__T("Music Video");
2710 else if (Value==__T("9")) Value=__T("Short Film");
2711 else if (Value==__T("10")) Value=__T("TV Show");
2712 else if (Value==__T("11")) Value=__T("Booklet");
2713 else if (Value==__T("14")) Value=__T("Ringtone");
2714 else if (Value==__T("21")) Value=__T("Podcast");
2715 else Value=__T("Unknown Type");
2716 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_ContentType, Value);
2717 }
2718 if (Parameter=="AppleStoreAccountType")
2719 {
2720 if (Value==__T("0"))
2721 Value=__T("iTunes");
2722 else
2723 Value=__T("AOL");
2724 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_ServiceName, Value);
2725 }
2726 if (Parameter=="Rating")
2727 {
2728 if (Value==__T("0")) Value=__T("None");
2729 else if (Value==__T("2")) Value=__T("Clean");
2730 else Value=__T("Explicit");
2731 }
2732 if (Parameter=="AppleStoreCountry")
2733 {
2734 if (Value==__T("143441")) Value=__T("United States");
2735 else if (Value==__T("143442")) Value=__T("France");
2736 else if (Value==__T("143443")) Value=__T("Germany");
2737 else if (Value==__T("143444")) Value=__T("United Kingdom");
2738 else if (Value==__T("143445")) Value=__T("Austria");
2739 else if (Value==__T("143446")) Value=__T("Belgium");
2740 else if (Value==__T("143447")) Value=__T("Finland");
2741 else if (Value==__T("143448")) Value=__T("Greece");
2742 else if (Value==__T("143449")) Value=__T("Ireland");
2743 else if (Value==__T("143450")) Value=__T("Italy");
2744 else if (Value==__T("143451")) Value=__T("Luxembourg");
2745 else if (Value==__T("143452")) Value=__T("Netherlands");
2746 else if (Value==__T("143453")) Value=__T("Portugal");
2747 else if (Value==__T("143454")) Value=__T("Spain");
2748 else if (Value==__T("143455")) Value=__T("Canada");
2749 else if (Value==__T("143456")) Value=__T("Sweden");
2750 else if (Value==__T("143457")) Value=__T("Norway");
2751 else if (Value==__T("143458")) Value=__T("Denmark");
2752 else if (Value==__T("143459")) Value=__T("Switzerland");
2753 else if (Value==__T("143460")) Value=__T("Australia");
2754 else if (Value==__T("143461")) Value=__T("New Zealand");
2755 else if (Value==__T("143462")) Value=__T("Japan");
2756 else Value=__T("Unknown Country");
2757 }
2758 if (!Parameter.empty())
2759 {
2760 Element_Info1(Parameter.c_str());
2761 if (Value!=Retrieve(Stream_General, 0, Parameter.c_str()))
2762 Fill(Stream_General, 0, Parameter.c_str(), Value);
2763 }
2764 FILLING_END();
2765 }
2766 break;
2767 case Elements::moov_meta_hdlr_mdta :
2768 if(!moov_udta_meta_keys_List.empty())
2769 {
2770 FILLING_BEGIN();
2771 std::string Parameter;
2772 Metadata_Get(Parameter, moov_udta_meta_keys_List[moov_udta_meta_keys_ilst_Pos<moov_udta_meta_keys_List.size()?moov_udta_meta_keys_ilst_Pos:moov_udta_meta_keys_List.size()-1]);
2773 if (Parameter=="com.apple.quicktime.version")
2774 Vendor_Version=Value.SubString(__T(""), __T(" "));
2775 else if (Parameter=="com.apple.quicktime.player.version")
2776 Vendor_Version=Value.SubString(__T(""), __T(" "));
2777 else if (Parameter=="com.apple.quicktime.comment")
2778 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Comment, Value, true);
2779 else if (Parameter=="com.apple.quicktime.description")
2780 Fill(Stream_General, 0, General_Description, Value, true);
2781 else if (Parameter=="com.apple.finalcutstudio.media.uuid")
2782 Fill(Stream_General, 0, "Media/UUID", Value);
2783 else if (Parameter=="com.apple.finalcutstudio.media.history.uuid")
2784 Fill(Stream_General, 0, "Media/History/UUID", Value);
2785 else if (!Parameter.empty())
2786 Fill(Stream_General, 0, Parameter.c_str(), Value, true);
2787 FILLING_END();
2788 moov_udta_meta_keys_ilst_Pos++;
2789 }
2790 else
2791 Param2("Keys atom is missing!", 0);
2792 break;
2793 case Elements::moov_udta_meta :
2794 {
2795 FILLING_BEGIN();
2796 std::string Parameter;
2797 Metadata_Get(Parameter, (int32u)Element_Code_Get(Element_Level-1));
2798 if (!Parameter.empty())
2799 Fill(Stream_General, 0, Parameter.c_str(), Value, true);
2800 FILLING_END();
2801 }
2802 default: ;
2803 }
2804}

2882//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
2883void File_Mpeg4::moov_mvhd()
2884{
2885 NAME_VERSION_FLAG("Movie header");
2886
2887 //Parsing
2888 Ztring Date_Created, Date_Modified;
2889 int64u Duration;
2890 float32 a, b, u, c, d, v, x, y, w;
2891 int32u Rate;
2892 int16u Volume;
2893 Get_DATE1904_DEPENDOFVERSION(Date_Created, "Creation time");
2894 Get_DATE1904_DEPENDOFVERSION(Date_Modified, "Modification time");
2895 Get_B4(moov_mvhd_TimeScale, "Time scale"); Param_Info1(Ztring::ToZtring(moov_mvhd_TimeScale)+__T(" Hz"));
2896 Get_B_DEPENDOFVERSION(Duration, "Duration"); Param_Info1C(moov_mvhd_TimeScale, Ztring::ToZtring((int64u)Duration*1000/moov_mvhd_TimeScale)+__T(" ms"));
2897 Get_B4 (Rate, "Preferred rate"); Param_Info1(Ztring::ToZtring(((float32)Rate)/0x10000));
2898 Get_B2 (Volume, "Preferred volume"); Param_Info1(Ztring::ToZtring(((float32)Volume)/0x100));
2899 Skip_XX(10, "Reserved");
2900 Element_Begin1("Matrix structure");
2901 Get_BFP4(16, a, "a (width scale)");
2902 Get_BFP4(16, b, "b (width rotate)");
2903 Get_BFP4( 2, u, "u (width angle)");
2904 Get_BFP4(16, c, "c (height rotate)");
2905 Get_BFP4(16, d, "d (height scale)");
2906 Get_BFP4( 2, v, "v (height angle)");
2907 Get_BFP4(16, x, "x (position left)");
2908 Get_BFP4(16, y, "y (position top)");
2909 Get_BFP4( 2, w, "w (divider)");
2910 Element_End0();
2911 Skip_B4( "Preview time");
2912 Skip_B4( "Preview duration");
2913 Skip_B4( "Poster time");
2914 Skip_B4( "Selection time");
2915 Skip_B4( "Selection duration");
2916 Skip_B4( "Current time");
2917 Skip_B4( "Next track ID");
2918
2919 FILLING_BEGIN();
2920 //if (moov_mvhd_TimeScale)
2921 //{
2922 //int32u Duration=(int32u)(((float)Duration)/TimeScale*1000);
2923 //Fill("Duration", Duration);
2924 //}
2925 if (Date_Created.find(__T('\r'))!=std::string::npos)
2926 Date_Created.resize(Date_Created.find(__T('\r')));
2927 if (Date_Created.find(__T('\n'))!=std::string::npos)
2928 Date_Created.resize(Date_Created.find(__T('\n')));
2929 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Encoded_Date", Date_Created);
2930 if (Date_Modified.find(__T('\r'))!=std::string::npos)
2931 Date_Modified.resize(Date_Modified.find(__T('\r')));
2932 if (Date_Modified.find(__T('\n'))!=std::string::npos)
2933 Date_Modified.resize(Date_Modified.find(__T('\n')));
2934 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Tagged_Date", Date_Modified);
2935 FILLING_END();
2936}

2938//---------------------------------------------------------------------------

2942

2946 moov_trak_tkhd_Width=0;
2947 moov_trak_tkhd_Height=0;
2948 moov_trak_tkhd_DisplayAspectRatio=0;
2949 moov_trak_tkhd_Rotation=0;

2953 ++StreamOrder;
2954 FILLING_END();
2955}

2963//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
2964void File_Mpeg4::moov_trak_edts_elst()
2965{
2966 NAME_VERSION_FLAG("Edit List");
2967
2968 //Parsing
2969 int32u Count;
2970 Get_B4 (Count, "Number of entries");
2971 for (int32u Pos=0; Pos<Count; Pos++)
2972 {
2973 stream::edts_struct edts;
2974 Element_Begin1("Entry");
2975 Get_B_DEPENDOFVERSION(edts.Duration, "Track duration"); Param_Info2C(moov_mvhd_TimeScale, (int64u)edts.Duration*1000/moov_mvhd_TimeScale, " ms");
2976 Get_B_DEPENDOFVERSION(edts.Delay, "Media time"); Param_Info2C(moov_mvhd_TimeScale && (edts.Delay!=(int32u)-1), (int64u)edts.Delay*1000/moov_mvhd_TimeScale, " ms");
2977 Get_B4 (edts.Rate, "Media rate"); Param_Info1(((float)edts.Rate)/0x10000);
2978 Element_End0();
2979
2980 Streams[moov_trak_tkhd_TrackID].edts.push_back(edts);
2981 }

3007//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
3008void File_Mpeg4::moov_trak_mdia_hdlr()
3009{
3010 NAME_VERSION_FLAG("Handler Reference");
3011
3012 //Parsing
3013 Ztring Title;
3014 int32u Type, SubType, Manufacturer;
3015 int8u Size;
3016 Get_C4 (Type, "Component type");
3017 Get_C4 (SubType, "Component subtype");
3018 Get_C4 (Manufacturer, "Component manufacturer");
3019 Skip_B4( "Component flags");
3020 Skip_B4( "Component flags mask");
3021 if (Element_Offset<Element_Size)
3022 {
3023 Peek_B1(Size);
3024 if (Element_Offset+1+Size==Element_Size)
3025 {
3026 Skip_B1( "Component name size");
3027 Get_Local(Size, Title, "Component name");
3028 }
3029 else
3030 {
3031 std::string TitleS;
3032 Get_String(Element_Size-Element_Offset, TitleS, "Component name");
3033 Title.From_UTF8(TitleS.c_str());
3034 if (Title.empty())
3035 Title.From_Local(TitleS.c_str()); //Trying Local...
3036 }
3037 if (Title.find(__T("Handler"))!=std::string::npos || Title.find(__T("handler"))!=std::string::npos || Title.find(__T("vide"))!=std::string::npos || Title.find(__T("soun"))!=std::string::npos || Title==Ztring().From_CC4(SubType))
3038 Title.clear(); //This is not a Title
3039 }
3040
3041 FILLING_BEGIN();
3042 if (!Title.empty() && Retrieve(Stream_General, 0, General_Title).empty()) Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Title", Title);
3043
3044 switch (SubType)
3045 {
3046 case Elements::moov_trak_mdia_hdlr_clcp :
3047 if (StreamKind_Last!=Stream_Text)
3048 {
3049 Stream_Prepare(Stream_Text);
3050 }
3051 break;
3052 case Elements::moov_trak_mdia_hdlr_data :
3053 if (StreamKind_Last!=Stream_Other)
3054 {
3055 Stream_Prepare(Stream_Other);
3056 Fill(Stream_Other, StreamPos_Last, Other_Type, "Data");
3057 }
3058 break;
3059 case Elements::moov_trak_mdia_hdlr_soun :
3060 if (StreamKind_Last!=Stream_Audio)
3061 {
3062 Stream_Prepare(Stream_Audio);
3063 }
3064 break;
3065 case Elements::moov_trak_mdia_hdlr_vide :
3066 if (StreamKind_Last!=Stream_Video)
3067 {
3068 Stream_Prepare(Stream_Video);
3069 }
3070 break;
3071 case Elements::moov_trak_mdia_hdlr_text :
3072 case Elements::moov_trak_mdia_hdlr_sbtl :
3073 if (StreamKind_Last!=Stream_Text)
3074 {
3075 if (Streams[moov_trak_tkhd_TrackID].IsChapter)
3076 Stream_Prepare(Stream_Menu);
3077 else
3078 {
3079 Stream_Prepare(Stream_Text);
3080 if (SubType!=Elements::moov_trak_mdia_hdlr_text)
3081 Fill(Stream_Text, StreamPos_Last, Text_MuxingMode, Ztring().From_CC4(SubType));
3082 }
3083 }
3084 break;
3085 case Elements::moov_trak_mdia_hdlr_twen :
3086 if (StreamKind_Last!=Stream_Text)
3087 {
3088 Stream_Prepare(Stream_Other);
3089 Fill(Stream_Other, StreamPos_Last, Other_Type, "Tween");
3090 }
3091 break;
3092 case Elements::moov_trak_mdia_hdlr_tmcd :
3093 if (StreamKind_Last!=Stream_Text)
3094 {
3095 Stream_Prepare(Stream_Other);
3096 Fill(Stream_Other, StreamPos_Last, Other_Type, "Time code");
3097 Fill(Stream_Other, StreamPos_Last, Other_Format, "QuickTime TC");
3098 }
3099 break;
3100 case Elements::moov_trak_mdia_hdlr_subp :
3101 if (StreamKind_Last!=Stream_Text)
3102 {
3103 Stream_Prepare(Stream_Text);
3104 CodecID_Fill(__T("subp"), Stream_Text, StreamPos_Last, InfoCodecID_Format_Mpeg4);
3105 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, Text_Codec, "subp");
3106 }
3107 break;
3108 case Elements::moov_trak_mdia_hdlr_subt :
3109 if (StreamKind_Last!=Stream_Text)
3110 {
3111 Stream_Prepare(Stream_Text);
3112 }
3113 break;
3114 case Elements::moov_trak_mdia_hdlr_MPEG :
3115 mdat_MustParse=true; //Data is in MDAT
3116 case Elements::moov_trak_mdia_hdlr_alis :
3117 //Stream_Prepare(Stream_Other);
3118 //Fill(Stream_Other, StreamPos_Last, Other_Type, "Alias"); //TODO: what is the meaning of such hdlr?
3119 break;
3120 case Elements::moov_trak_mdia_hdlr_hint :
3121 if (StreamKind_Last==Stream_Max) //Note: some files have both vmhd and hmhd, I don't know the meaning of such header, so skipping hmhd for the moment
3122 {
3123 Stream_Prepare(Stream_Other);
3124 Fill(Stream_Other, StreamPos_Last, Other_Type, "Hint");
3125 Streams[moov_trak_tkhd_TrackID].StreamKind=Stream_Other;
3126 Streams[moov_trak_tkhd_TrackID].StreamPos=StreamPos_Last;
3127 }
3128 break;
3129 case Elements::moov_trak_mdia_hdlr_ocsm :
3130 if (StreamKind_Last!=Stream_Other)
3131 Stream_Prepare(Stream_Other);
3132 Fill(Stream_Other, StreamPos_Last, Other_Type, "Object content information");
3133 break;
3134 case Elements::moov_trak_mdia_hdlr_odsm :
3135 if (StreamKind_Last!=Stream_Other)
3136 Stream_Prepare(Stream_Other);
3137 Fill(Stream_Other, StreamPos_Last, Other_Type, "Object description");
3138 break;
3139 case Elements::moov_trak_mdia_hdlr_sdsm :
3140 if (StreamKind_Last!=Stream_Other)
3141 Stream_Prepare(Stream_Other);
3142 Fill(Stream_Other, StreamPos_Last, Other_Type, "Scene description");
3143 break;
3144 default:
3145 if (!Streams[moov_trak_tkhd_TrackID].hdlr_SubType) //TODO: check what is the best method to detect SubType (moov_trak_mdia_hdlr vs moov_trak_mdia_minf_hdlr)
3146 {
3147 Streams[moov_trak_tkhd_TrackID].hdlr_Type=Type;
3148 Streams[moov_trak_tkhd_TrackID].hdlr_SubType=SubType;
3149 Streams[moov_trak_tkhd_TrackID].hdlr_Manufacturer=Manufacturer;
3150 }
3151 }
3152
3153 if (StreamKind_Last!=Stream_Max)
3154 {
3155 Streams[moov_trak_tkhd_TrackID].StreamKind=StreamKind_Last;
3156 Streams[moov_trak_tkhd_TrackID].StreamPos=StreamPos_Last;
3157 }
3158
3159 if (Manufacturer!=0x00000000)
3160 {
3161 if (Vendor==0x00000000)
3162 Vendor=Manufacturer;
3163 else if (Vendor!=Manufacturer)
3164 Vendor=0xFFFFFFFF; //Two names, this is two much
3165 }
3166 FILLING_END();
3167}

3229//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
3230void File_Mpeg4::moov_trak_mdia_mdhd()
3231{
3232 NAME_VERSION_FLAG("Media Header");
3233
3234 //Parsing
3235 Ztring Date_Created, Date_Modified;
3236 int64u Duration;
3237 int32u TimeScale;
3238 int16u Language;
3239 Get_DATE1904_DEPENDOFVERSION(Date_Created, "Creation time");
3240 Get_DATE1904_DEPENDOFVERSION(Date_Modified, "Modification time");
3241 Get_B4(TimeScale, "Time scale");
3242 Get_B_DEPENDOFVERSION(Duration, "Duration"); Param_Info2C(TimeScale, Duration*1000/TimeScale, " ms");
3243 Get_B2 (Language, "Language"); Param_Info1(Language_Get(Language));
3244 Skip_B2( "Quality");
3245
3246 FILLING_BEGIN();
3247 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Language", Language_Get(Language));
3248 Streams[moov_trak_tkhd_TrackID].mdhd_Duration=Duration;
3249 Streams[moov_trak_tkhd_TrackID].mdhd_TimeScale=TimeScale;
3250
3251 //Coherency tests
3252 if (Streams[moov_trak_tkhd_TrackID].tkhd_Duration*1.01>=Duration*0.99 && Streams[moov_trak_tkhd_TrackID].tkhd_Duration*0.99<=Duration*1.01 && TimeScale && moov_mvhd_TimeScale!=TimeScale && moov_mvhd_TimeScale)
3253 {
3254 float64 Ratio=((float64)TimeScale)/((float64)moov_mvhd_TimeScale);
3255 Streams[moov_trak_tkhd_TrackID].tkhd_Duration=float64_int64s(Streams[moov_trak_tkhd_TrackID].tkhd_Duration/Ratio);
3256 Clear(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Duration_Source");
3257 Fill(StreamKind_Last, StreamPos_Last, "Duration", float64_int64s(((float64)Streams[moov_trak_tkhd_TrackID].tkhd_Duration)*1000/((float64)moov_mvhd_TimeScale)), 10, true);
3258 }
3259 FILLING_END();
3260}

3290//---------------------------------------------------------------------------
3291void File_Mpeg4::moov_trak_mdia_minf_code_sean_RU_A()
3292{
3293 Element_Name("RU*A (found in Avid?)");
3294
3295 //Parsing
3296 Ztring Path;
3297 Skip_B4( "Unknown");
3298 Skip_B4( "Unknown");
3299 Skip_B4( "Unknown");
3300 Get_Local(Element_Size-Element_Offset, Path, "Path?");
3301
3302 FILLING_BEGIN();
3303 Streams[moov_trak_tkhd_TrackID].File_Name=Path;
3304 FILLING_END();
